Four theatres were closed and patients who were scheduled for surgery were transferred to nearby hospitals. JOHANNESBURG - The Gauteng Health Department says it has now repaired all theatres at the Thelle Mogoerane Hospital, formerly known as Natalspruit, on the East Rand.Four theatres were closed and patients who were scheduled for surgery were transferred to nearby hospitals.This comes after 40 patients were discovered to be infected with sepsis after operations at the hospital.The department s Steve Mabona says: After realising that the doors are not fully functioning, we took the decision that we are going to close the theatres to ensure we fix the doors. The theatres are now fully functional. We will not risk an infection with any patient. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)